This paper deals with higher-order rewriting, which is a topic in both logic and programming languages. The paper discusses the extension of higher-order algebraic specification languages, which is a topic in logic and formal methods (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the extension of Combinatory Rewrite Systems (CRSs), which is a topic in programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The paper also discusses termination and confluence, which are topics in software engineering (cs.SE), formal languages (cs.FL), and data structures (cs.DS). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO, followed by cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, and cs.DS.
